      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:55:13",
      "text": [
        " غُلَامٍ دَخَلَ دَارَ قَوْمٍ فَوَقَعَ فِي الْبِئْرِ فَقَالَ إِنْ كَانُوا مُتَّهَمِينَ ضَمِنُوا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, raising it, ",
          "Regarding a boy who entered a house of a people, so he fell down into well. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘If they were suspicious, they would be responsible’."
        ]
      }
